expectancy of the general popula-tion. HIV is now a chronic treatable disease 
and requires a multidisciplinary approach that includes both the hospital 
medicine specialties and primary care physicians. The fragmented model to 
provide social and medical healthcare hinders the proper management of patients 
with HIV infection. There is significant clinical and geographical variability 
in the healthcare provided for HIV infection in Spain and the need to define and 
implement new models of healthcare delivery for this disease has been 
identified.

