survival (hazard ratio (HR): 1.311; 95% confidence interval (CI): 1.117-1.538; 
p = 0.001) and (HR: 1.358; 95% CI: 1.152-1.601; p < 0.001), respectively.
CONCLUSION: This study showed both NLR and PLR to be independently associated 
with survival in patients who were treated for skeletal metastasis.

