BACKGROUND: Osteogenic sarcoma of the skull is uncommon and long-term outcome is 
not well defined. We review the literature and present a pediatric case of 
calvarial osteogenic sarcoma with good long-term oncological and cosmetic 
outcome and excellent quality of life. This case presented major surgical 
challenges, which are detailed.
CASE DESCRIPTION: A 6-year-old boy presented with a painless 5 cm × 5 cm lump 
